                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>R. T. Massie, son of Nathaniel Massie of Augusta, died. A graduate of the
                    University of Virginia, he was assistant professor of mathematics there before
                    becoming full professor at Randolph Macon College and at the University of
                    Virginia. The editor credits him with being perhaps the finest mathematician his
                    age in the Confederacy.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
