                <head>A Female Spy</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Kelly</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Mrs.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>This short article refers to the letter published on page one about the
                    travels of a Union officer's wife through the Shenandoah Valley. The editor
                    praises Mrs. Kelly of Staunton and Mrs. Kennedy for their participation in the
                    deception of a female spy and warns that others might be more easily taken in by
                    the spy.</summary>
                <note/>
