                </names>
                <summary>Rev. Mr. Harvy, Chaplain of the 110th Ohio Regiment, was taken at
                    Winchester. Evidence reveals that he helped slaves run away, in one case aiding
                    in the escape of Sarah Jenkins, a slave of W. J. Shumate of Augusta County. The
                    Richmond Enquirer requests that he be handed over to state civil authorities at
                    once in order to be prosecuted.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
